<p><b>Errol Morris</b> (born <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="1948-02-05"><span class="mw-formatted-date" title="02-05"><a href="/wiki/February_5" title="February 5">February 5</a></span>, <a href="/wiki/1948" title="1948">1948</a></span>) is an <a href="/wiki/United_States" title="United States">American</a> <a href="/wiki/Academy_Awards" title="Academy Awards" class="mw-redirect">Academy Award</a> winning <a href="/wiki/Documentary_film" title="Documentary film">documentary film</a> director. In 2003 <i><a href="/wiki/The_Guardian" title="The Guardian">The Guardian</a></i> listed him as number seven in their <a href="http://film.guardian.co.uk/features/page/0,11456,1082823,00.html" class="external text" title="http://film.guardian.co.uk/features/page/0,11456,1082823,00.html" rel="nofollow">list</a> of the world's 40 best directors.</p>
